Jeff Wicks, News24iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - A Kloof man pleaded guilty to 1 132 counts of possession of child pornography and received a suspended sentence on Thursday.&nbsp; He was also given a R30 000 fine.Police spokesperson Lieutenant Nqobile Gwala said that 39-year-old Matthy Zondagh was handed a R30 000 fine and ten years imprisonment, wholly suspended for five years, by the Pinetown Magistrates Court."Members of the Project Spiderweb acted on intelligence driven information and a search and seizure operation was conducted at Kloof in April last year. The accused was found at his house in possession of a memory stick containing child pornography images," she said."He was then placed under arrest and charged with possessing child pornography. He made several court appearances until his sentence. He pleaded guilty to 1 132 counts of possession of child pornography," she added.KwaZulu-Natal Police Commissioner Mmamonnye Ngobeni said: "Parents should keep a close eye on who their children are chatting to on social networks, what they are chatting about and the pictures they are sharing. This sentence is a proof that criminals cannot get away after committing such misdeeds."24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.